WEBVTT

00:01.560 --> 00:04.561
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

00:04.580 --> 00:06.396
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:06.398 --> 00:07.655
Oh.

00:07.733 --> 00:10.751
Hello.
(chuckles)

00:10.827 --> 00:12.419
-Oh.
-Is that for both of us?

00:12.571 --> 00:17.016
-No. That's my breakfast.
-Oh.

00:17.167 --> 00:19.426
Okay, you know,
people used to eat like this.

00:19.578 --> 00:22.929
I got my toast, my butter,
my whole milk,

00:23.082 --> 00:26.025
scrambled eggs, bacon,
ham slice,

00:26.101 --> 00:28.268
some hash browns,
and got a little oatmeal.

00:28.345 --> 00:30.771
Well, then, um,
bon appétit.

00:30.847 --> 00:32.865
-Thank you.
-(chuckles)

00:32.941 --> 00:37.127
Hey, uh, well, I tried
to call Mel, and--

00:37.129 --> 00:39.187
And it didn't go through.

00:39.265 --> 00:41.540
No, it wouldn't.

00:41.617 --> 00:44.359
It's not up to me.
It's the island.

00:44.436 --> 00:46.170
I'm sorry.

00:47.697 --> 00:51.275
(scoffs) Okay, well, is it,
I mean, impossible?

00:51.293 --> 00:52.609
Ruby, I-I wish I could.

00:52.628 --> 00:54.611
-(helicopter rumbling overhead)
-Ruby, honestly,

00:54.630 --> 00:55.779
I wish I could--

00:55.781 --> 00:58.706
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

00:58.726 --> 01:02.636
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:02.730 --> 01:04.879
Oh, I-I think it's landing.

01:04.899 --> 01:05.972
Oh.

01:06.125 --> 01:09.626
PERSON:
Thank you for the ride!

01:09.686 --> 01:11.962
Ah!
(laughs)

01:11.964 --> 01:14.406
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:14.558 --> 01:16.983
Eileen Mitchell, I presume.

01:17.060 --> 01:18.577
That was unexpected.

01:18.728 --> 01:20.746
Yeah. I-I was so excited
to get here

01:20.823 --> 01:23.156
that I just showed up
two hours early for the plane.

01:23.250 --> 01:24.474
Oh.

01:24.476 --> 01:25.976
And this big fellow
was just sitting there,

01:25.994 --> 01:28.253
and so I whipped out
my credit card,

01:28.330 --> 01:30.905
and here I am--
paradise.

01:30.925 --> 01:34.927
Now, where can I get
a martini?

01:35.078 --> 01:37.763
(humming happily)

01:37.990 --> 01:38.989
Ooh.

01:39.007 --> 01:45.753
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:45.831 --> 01:48.682
<i> (light music)</i>

01:48.834 --> 01:55.739
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:02.197 --> 02:04.456
EILEEN: I haven't been
in a helicopter since--

02:04.533 --> 02:07.200
Oh, I don't know.
It must have been early '80s.

02:07.353 --> 02:08.943
Oh, yeah, Annie Leibovitz.

02:09.037 --> 02:13.781
She had me on a rooftop,
New York, in December.

02:13.801 --> 02:17.043
I got pneumonia.
The client loved it.

02:17.120 --> 02:19.138
Um, please have a seat,
Mrs. Mitchell.

02:19.214 --> 02:22.624
I'm your host, Elena Roarke,
and this is my associate.

02:22.701 --> 02:24.217
Yes. Hi. I'm Ruby.

02:24.294 --> 02:26.052
Oh, it's just lovely
to meet you.

02:26.205 --> 02:27.371
-Do you model?
-Huh?

02:27.389 --> 02:30.816
I was a model.
It's a terrible job, though.

02:30.967 --> 02:33.134
Not nearly as glamorous
as it seems.

02:33.212 --> 02:34.820
And once you're a woman
of a certain age,

02:34.897 --> 02:36.897
people don't want
to look at you anyway.

02:37.049 --> 02:38.991
And then once you're a woman
of a certain
<i> certain</i>
age,

02:39.142 --> 02:41.309
they simply
don't see you at all.

02:41.387 --> 02:43.220
Well, um, that must be painful.

02:43.238 --> 02:45.222
Well, I try not to dwell.

02:45.224 --> 02:47.057
Regardless, it's Ms. Mitchell,

02:47.075 --> 02:50.335
currently unattached,
but please call me Eileen.

02:50.412 --> 02:51.503
(all chuckle)

02:51.655 --> 02:54.414
Well, Eileen,
what can the island do for you?

02:54.491 --> 02:57.751
Mmm!
Oh, now, that's a martini.

02:57.827 --> 02:59.419
(laughs)

02:59.496 --> 03:01.496
(sighs)
About a year ago,

03:01.590 --> 03:05.575
my daughter Theodora
cut me out of her life.

03:05.594 --> 03:07.168
And why did she do that?

03:07.246 --> 03:10.263
Well, there may have been
a small incident.

03:10.340 --> 03:13.007
I was watching
my grandson Frederich,

03:13.085 --> 03:15.510
and after he was sound asleep,

03:15.529 --> 03:17.679
I popped next door
for a little karaoke.

03:17.698 --> 03:20.014
So you left
your sleeping grandson

03:20.034 --> 03:21.700
at the house by himself?

03:21.702 --> 03:25.520
Sound asleep,
safe in his crib.

03:25.539 --> 03:27.706
And that party needed
my attention,

03:27.783 --> 03:29.766
far more than Fredrick did.

03:29.785 --> 03:31.952
Well, my daughter--
she acted like I left the kid

03:32.104 --> 03:34.195
at a bus station
with a "kidnap me" sign

03:34.215 --> 03:35.288
around his neck.

03:35.441 --> 03:37.090
ELENA: And you feel
like that was unfair?

03:37.200 --> 03:39.109
I was young when I had Theo,

03:39.127 --> 03:41.202
and I didn't want
to be one of those mothers

03:41.255 --> 03:44.890
who was always away,
and so I took Theodora with me.

03:44.967 --> 03:48.118
Ah, she was my best friend...

03:48.120 --> 03:49.561
my little backpack.

03:49.713 --> 03:52.305
I gave her a childhood
of culture, adventure.

03:52.399 --> 03:54.399
She speaks three languages,
you know.

03:54.551 --> 03:56.235
-Great.
-But ever since she had Freddy,

03:56.386 --> 03:57.677
I mean, she thinks

03:57.755 --> 04:00.130
that every one of
my parenting choices was wrong,

04:00.148 --> 04:02.574
and not just wrong--awful.

04:02.651 --> 04:05.151
So your fantasy is?

04:05.228 --> 04:07.412
My fantasy is simple.

04:07.564 --> 04:11.157
I want to be with my daughter
and her family again.

04:11.310 --> 04:14.753
I miss her. I miss them...
with my whole being.

04:14.980 --> 04:16.980
Well, fantasies
are rarely simple,

04:16.999 --> 04:19.649
but you're gonna be very happy
to know that I have arranged

04:19.668 --> 04:22.152
for Theo, David,
and Freddy to be on the island.

04:22.154 --> 04:24.337
They're here? Now?

04:24.490 --> 04:25.989
Ah!

04:25.991 --> 04:27.340
Why don't you go to your room
and freshen up?

04:27.493 --> 04:28.934
Meet me at the mangroves
in an hour.

04:29.011 --> 04:30.494
That's where your fantasy
will begin.

04:30.512 --> 04:32.104
-Just like that?
-ELENA: Just like that.

04:32.255 --> 04:34.106
Welcome to Fantasy Island.

04:34.182 --> 04:36.424
Oh, thank you Elaine.

04:36.518 --> 04:37.592
Ah, Elena.

04:37.611 --> 04:41.505
No, it's Eileen.
(giggles)

04:41.523 --> 04:45.784
Oh, I hope the island's
not too hard on her.

04:45.861 --> 04:49.121
She just wants to be
with her family.

04:49.197 --> 04:52.516
She does, but it's also
more than that.

04:52.534 --> 04:55.702
In any case,
she'll get what she needs.

04:55.779 --> 04:59.372
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

04:59.449 --> 05:06.120
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:06.198 --> 05:08.048
(knock at door)

05:08.200 --> 05:10.291
-May we come in?
-Oh, of course.

05:10.369 --> 05:12.886
And excuse the mess.
I was just unpacking.

05:12.962 --> 05:14.796
ELENA: Not at all,
Professor Wakefield.

05:14.873 --> 05:17.207
(laughs)
I'm your host, Elena Roarke,

05:17.300 --> 05:18.800
and this is
my associate Ruby.

05:18.877 --> 05:20.802
-Yes. Hi.
-(both chuckle)

05:20.804 --> 05:23.989
Wow.
Now, look at that.

05:24.066 --> 05:28.309
My husband, he was--I mean, he
is an amateur astronomer, so...

05:28.329 --> 05:29.736
Oh, then he'll be watching

05:29.888 --> 05:31.330
the asteroid
tomorrow night, too.

05:31.406 --> 05:34.074
Yes.
Yeah, I'm--I'm sure he will.

05:34.226 --> 05:37.669
So, Professor Wakefield,
what can the island do for you?

05:37.746 --> 05:40.038
As you know,
I'm a scientist.

05:40.115 --> 05:41.915
Yes, you're
a particle physicist.

05:42.067 --> 05:44.568
Yes. I spent many years
on a team

05:44.570 --> 05:47.012
searching
for a subatomic particle

05:47.014 --> 05:48.013
known as the Higgs boson.

05:48.164 --> 05:49.756
The God particle.

05:49.833 --> 05:51.741
Mm, that's what the media
called it,

05:51.760 --> 05:53.852
but I studied it a long time.

05:53.929 --> 05:55.428
It's not God.

05:55.581 --> 05:58.523
Okay, um,
and that disappointed you?

06:00.194 --> 06:01.360
I was in second grade

06:01.511 --> 06:03.010
when I first looked
into a microscope

06:03.030 --> 06:06.347
and saw a cell
from the skin of an onion.

06:06.367 --> 06:07.440
I was hooked.

06:07.517 --> 06:09.926
I committed my life
to going deeper.

06:09.928 --> 06:13.597
Everything
in the universe is...

06:13.615 --> 06:15.265
explainable,

06:15.283 --> 06:18.618
and I've come to find that...

06:18.770 --> 06:20.695
almost unbearable.

06:20.714 --> 06:23.790
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

06:23.867 --> 06:25.942
My fantasy
is to experience something

06:25.944 --> 06:28.461
I can't explain
through science,

06:28.614 --> 06:29.963
to know with certainty

06:30.115 --> 06:32.616
that there is
something greater out there.

06:32.634 --> 06:35.802
That's a tall order,
but I absolutely believe

06:35.954 --> 06:37.137
that we can help you.

06:37.289 --> 06:38.730
Ms. Roarke, I should warn you,

06:38.807 --> 06:40.624
I'm about as skeptical
as they come.

06:40.626 --> 06:42.550
Ah, it's okay.
I can work with that.

06:42.569 --> 06:45.404
-(laughs)
-Welcome to Fantasy Island.

06:45.480 --> 06:48.632
And, Professor,
do try to have some fun.

06:48.634 --> 06:50.467
(sighs)

06:50.485 --> 06:53.245
<i> (soft music)</i>

06:53.321 --> 06:56.473
(laughter, indistinct chatter)

06:56.491 --> 07:03.237
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:03.315 --> 07:07.092
I can't believe they're here.
It's really them, right?

07:07.243 --> 07:11.154
I mean, not--not actors
or androids or anything?

07:11.173 --> 07:12.989
Well, I-I thought
about androids, yes,

07:12.991 --> 07:15.917
but it turned out to be cheaper
to just spring for the airfare.

07:15.994 --> 07:17.919
-Can I go to them?
-Yeah.

07:17.938 --> 07:20.755
You can, but, Eileen,
a word of warning--

07:20.832 --> 07:23.516
Oh, look how big he got.

07:23.669 --> 07:26.853
He was a baby,
and now he looks like a boy.

07:26.930 --> 07:30.449
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:30.525 --> 07:31.616
Theodora?

07:31.768 --> 07:35.436
-(child babbles)
-Theodora, it's your mother.

07:35.514 --> 07:37.013
THEODORA AND DAVID:
Oh!

07:37.032 --> 07:40.350
(laughs)

07:40.352 --> 07:43.520
All right.
I see how it is.

07:43.538 --> 07:45.780
You know, I am not
going to make a scene.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.524
I mean, I only arranged
this trip

07:47.526 --> 07:49.859
so we could start over
as a family.

07:49.878 --> 07:52.119
But if you honestly think
ignoring me

07:52.197 --> 07:54.789
is the most mature course
of action here,

07:54.866 --> 07:58.384
then who am I to challenge you?

07:58.537 --> 07:59.478
(gasps)

07:59.629 --> 08:00.870
It's way past lunch.
Let's head inside.

08:00.889 --> 08:02.038
THEO:
Okay.

08:02.131 --> 08:04.966
All right, now,
t-this is cruel, Theodora.

08:05.043 --> 08:09.379
I mean, am I honestly so awful
that you can't even look at me?

08:09.397 --> 08:11.564
-FREDDY: Mama.
-Theodora?

08:11.641 --> 08:13.883
Theodora, come back here!

08:13.885 --> 08:16.828
What the hell
is happening here?

08:16.905 --> 08:19.146
My family is completely
ignoring me.

08:19.166 --> 08:20.740
I mean, why did they come

08:20.834 --> 08:22.909
if they didn't want
to see me, hmm?

08:23.061 --> 08:26.913
-I tried to tell you, Eileen.
-Tell me what?

08:26.990 --> 08:29.082
Would you mind getting me
my bookmark?

08:29.084 --> 08:30.658
It's over there--little table.
You see the--

08:30.736 --> 08:31.901
-Really?
-Yes, please.

08:31.920 --> 08:33.419
In front of the mirror.
Thank you so much.

08:33.496 --> 08:35.572
You know
she completely blanked me?

08:35.590 --> 08:36.681
I mean, it was impressive.

08:36.833 --> 08:38.499
Almost as if I were...

08:38.577 --> 08:41.186
<i> (light music)</i>

08:41.337 --> 08:45.524
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:45.675 --> 08:48.434
Invisible.

08:48.587 --> 08:50.086
There...

08:50.088 --> 08:52.346
now you get it.

08:52.366 --> 08:54.015
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:54.034 --> 08:55.534
Whoa.

09:02.158 --> 09:06.770
So you're the only one
who can see and hear me?

09:06.788 --> 09:08.938
I can see you.
Hi.

09:08.940 --> 09:09.881
Oh, hello.

09:09.958 --> 09:11.716
It is just
so comforting to know

09:11.868 --> 09:14.627
that two whole people
can see me.

09:14.780 --> 09:16.370
So what now?

09:16.390 --> 09:18.205
-Okay, and so she...
-Is invisible.

09:18.225 --> 09:19.540
-Yeah.
-EILEEN: Yeah.

09:19.560 --> 09:21.375
Apparently it's not enough
that I feel invisible.

09:21.395 --> 09:24.287
Now I get to be invisible
as well.

09:24.306 --> 09:25.897
Eileen, uh,
you seem triggered.

09:26.049 --> 09:27.791
Maybe this is something
we should examine?

09:27.809 --> 09:30.126
-I don't want to examine it.
-Okay.

09:30.145 --> 09:32.887
I want to turn things around
with Theodora,

09:32.981 --> 09:36.649
and I can't do that,
if I can't talk to her.

09:36.802 --> 09:38.301
I believe you spent time

09:38.303 --> 09:40.245
at an ashram, right,
in Costa Rica?

09:40.322 --> 09:42.414
What? Do you know
everything about me?

09:42.565 --> 09:45.475
Yes, I did.
It was a long time ago.

09:45.568 --> 09:47.994
And you had a guru over there.
Her name was Satnam.

09:47.996 --> 09:51.164
What do you think she'll say
is the point of all of this?

09:51.258 --> 09:54.968
-She never said anything.
-Hmm.

09:56.504 --> 09:57.821
What?

09:57.823 --> 10:00.432
I'm not supposed to talk?

10:00.583 --> 10:04.085
-I'm just supposed to listen?
-Mm-hmm.

10:04.162 --> 10:06.938
Oh, I'm sorry, Javier.
We have a guest.

10:07.015 --> 10:09.256
What--what guest?

10:09.276 --> 10:12.760
You know, I spent four hours
at the pickup point--no guest.

10:12.838 --> 10:14.687
Did you even think of calling?

10:14.764 --> 10:18.191
He's cute.
Are you two an item?

10:18.267 --> 10:20.526
-No.
-(scoffs) Okay.

10:20.603 --> 10:22.178
I'm sorry.
I should have called.

10:22.197 --> 10:24.197
But our guest--
she chartered a helicopter

10:24.349 --> 10:25.515
because she didn't want
to wait.

10:25.533 --> 10:26.941
Yeah, a-and to be fair,

10:26.960 --> 10:30.019
I mean, we didn't even know
until she arrived.

10:30.021 --> 10:32.464
Well, tell her she's
pretty damn inconsiderate.

10:34.209 --> 10:36.176
Well, he's a bit huffy.

10:38.697 --> 10:42.548
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:42.550 --> 10:45.702
Here I am, listening.
Listen, listen, listen.

10:45.704 --> 10:48.388
THEO: (laughing) Okay.
Let's get the ball.

10:48.540 --> 10:50.874
DAVID:
All right. Throw it back.

10:50.892 --> 10:52.542
(laughs)

10:52.560 --> 10:54.878
This place reminds me
so much of Bali.

10:54.880 --> 10:58.548
Did I ever tell you
about my three-legged monkey?

10:58.566 --> 10:59.883
His name was...

10:59.901 --> 11:01.809
-Khaki.
-Khaki.

11:01.828 --> 11:03.161
-No.
-I did, too.

11:03.312 --> 11:04.663
EILEEN:
Oh, that poor animal--

11:04.814 --> 11:09.058
He was a long-tail macaque,
and I was obsessed with him.

11:09.060 --> 11:11.152
And Eileen was
okay with that?

11:11.171 --> 11:13.487
I'm not sure she even noticed.

11:13.565 --> 11:17.567
Theodora, I chased down
that monkey so many times.

11:17.569 --> 11:19.752
No, that's not fair.

11:19.829 --> 11:22.514
She made him a collar and leash

11:22.665 --> 11:26.409
out of an old watchband
and a silk belt,

11:26.411 --> 11:28.520
and we used to say
that he was the most...

11:28.671 --> 11:34.417
-BOTH: Stylish monkey in town.
-(laughs)

11:34.419 --> 11:35.694
You miss her.

11:36.938 --> 11:40.757
Of course I miss her.
She's my mom.

11:40.759 --> 11:42.867
I miss you more, sweetheart.

11:42.944 --> 11:44.777
DAVID: Look how freakin'
adorable this one is.

11:44.930 --> 11:46.037
-THEO: Aw.
-DAVID: Huh?

11:46.114 --> 11:49.523
I could, uh, send it to her.

11:49.543 --> 11:50.950
No.

11:51.027 --> 11:52.544
David...

11:52.695 --> 11:54.954
how many times
have we given her an inch

11:55.031 --> 11:56.381
and watched her take ten miles?

11:56.532 --> 11:59.033
(scoffs)
I had more than enough chaos

11:59.110 --> 12:00.719
and abandonment growing up.

12:00.795 --> 12:02.462
I don't want it
in Freddy's life.

12:02.614 --> 12:03.722
Oh, honey.

12:03.798 --> 12:07.283
That's your choice.

12:07.302 --> 12:09.561
I set my boundaries
with my mom for a reason,

12:09.563 --> 12:11.563
and, yes, it's sad,

12:11.639 --> 12:13.565
but she left our baby alone

12:13.716 --> 12:16.050
because she couldn't stand
not being center of attention

12:16.069 --> 12:17.627
for five minutes.

12:17.629 --> 12:19.053
She made her choice,

12:19.072 --> 12:21.147
and I choose not
to keep allowing her

12:21.224 --> 12:22.615
to wreak havoc in our lives.

12:24.652 --> 12:27.561
(Freddy babbling excitedly)

12:27.581 --> 12:29.497
(Theodora laughs)

12:31.659 --> 12:33.251
FREDDY:
Mommy.

12:33.328 --> 12:34.477
Hey, babe.

12:34.479 --> 12:37.905
ELENA: The club sandwich
is excellent

12:37.924 --> 12:40.091
but unlikely to defy science.

12:40.318 --> 12:41.834
CHARLES:
Mm, to be honest,

12:41.911 --> 12:45.004
I'm not expecting anything
to do that.

12:45.098 --> 12:47.581
Can I ask, why did you come

12:47.659 --> 12:50.751
if you believe
your fantasy's not possible?

12:50.771 --> 12:52.437
I...

12:52.588 --> 12:55.515
don't have a good answer
to that question.

12:55.609 --> 12:57.091
Hope, perhaps?

12:57.110 --> 13:00.094
The same thing that kept you
searching for the God particle

13:00.171 --> 13:01.687
all those years.

13:01.840 --> 13:02.930
Perhaps.

13:03.174 --> 13:06.100
The difference is that then
you were searching,

13:06.119 --> 13:09.954
and now you're just eating
a club sandwich.

13:10.031 --> 13:11.498
I see your point.

13:13.018 --> 13:16.019
You know, the south end
of the beach

13:16.021 --> 13:18.021
is beautiful.

13:18.023 --> 13:22.041
I'm actually
going there right now.

13:22.193 --> 13:24.636
Enjoy your club sandwich,
Professor.

13:24.712 --> 13:27.680
(indistinct chatter)

13:29.050 --> 13:32.035
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

13:32.053 --> 13:33.719
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:33.796 --> 13:35.555
Isn't it beautiful?

13:35.631 --> 13:38.057
You should change the name
of this island

13:38.134 --> 13:41.894
from Fantasy Island
to Nightmare Hellscape Island.

13:41.971 --> 13:43.729
(chuckles)
Is something wrong?

13:43.806 --> 13:45.214
Oh, no, nothing's wrong.

13:45.216 --> 13:46.549
I'm fine.
I'm--

13:46.568 --> 13:49.160
Beautiful weather,
family who hates me.

13:49.237 --> 13:50.644
Do you know what she said?

13:50.664 --> 13:52.664
-I--
-She said I wreak havoc.

13:52.815 --> 13:53.814
Me!

13:53.834 --> 13:55.408
What did I do to her, Elaine?

13:55.560 --> 13:56.909
Elena.

13:57.062 --> 13:59.653
She said that she had
to set up "boundaries"

13:59.731 --> 14:02.565
because I take ten miles.

14:02.567 --> 14:07.328
I gave Theodora a memorable,
meaningful childhood.

14:07.347 --> 14:09.663
Screw her for not
appreciating it

14:09.683 --> 14:12.499
and you
for taking her side.

14:12.577 --> 14:14.143
Come with me.

14:19.767 --> 14:21.434
What the hell is this?

14:21.510 --> 14:22.861
A gift.

14:23.012 --> 14:25.438
You see your life with Theo
through your lens.

14:25.532 --> 14:28.515
This is an opportunity
to see it the way she did.

14:28.535 --> 14:31.536
The Golden Lotus?
Are we in Costa Rica?

14:31.613 --> 14:33.371
I need you to lower
your voice, please.

14:33.448 --> 14:35.932
This is a place
of silent contemplation.

14:35.950 --> 14:39.002
-They can hear me?
-No, but I can.

14:40.772 --> 14:44.123
EILEEN: This place touched
such a deep part of my soul.

14:44.200 --> 14:47.777
It's one of the places you
felt comfortable leaving Theo.

14:47.779 --> 14:49.795
She absolutely loved it here.

14:49.948 --> 14:53.057
(sniffling, crying softly)

14:54.895 --> 14:56.728
Did she?

15:02.385 --> 15:06.129
(crying softly, sniffles)

15:06.131 --> 15:08.631
That's Theo.

15:08.650 --> 15:12.243
What's wrong with her,
and why isn't anyone helping?

15:20.587 --> 15:22.420
Oh, Theodora.

15:22.571 --> 15:25.423
<i> (somber music)</i>

15:25.500 --> 15:28.167
If you don't see her
coming up the road by now,

15:28.319 --> 15:29.652
she won't be back today.

15:29.654 --> 15:31.930
THEO: Five more minutes.
Please, Satnam.

15:32.006 --> 15:33.932
I'm sure your
mother's fine, Theo.

15:34.083 --> 15:36.601
I know she's fine.

15:36.752 --> 15:39.162
She's always fine.

15:39.164 --> 15:43.424
It's just what if she
doesn't come back this time?

15:43.501 --> 15:49.447
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:49.598 --> 15:51.265
Come on.

15:51.342 --> 15:54.543
Gurmuk made chocolate cake.

15:54.545 --> 15:58.105
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:58.183 --> 15:59.773
Theo, wait!

15:59.851 --> 16:01.608
I had no idea
you felt that way!

16:01.628 --> 16:03.777
Please, honey, let me explain!

16:03.797 --> 16:05.463
Theo!

16:09.970 --> 16:11.803
She loved Costa Rica.

16:11.954 --> 16:13.546
I don't even think
she was there

16:13.622 --> 16:14.955
to see me off when I left.

16:14.975 --> 16:17.883
She was too cool for me,
even then.

16:17.960 --> 16:21.887
Or maybe she couldn't bear
to watch you leave her again.

16:21.964 --> 16:25.374
Like when you left her in
Amsterdam, Eileen, or in Bali

16:25.393 --> 16:26.985
and at a convent
at the Pyrenees.

16:27.103 --> 16:28.987
-I was making a living.
-So when Theo was crying

16:29.138 --> 16:31.656
into Gurmuk's chocolate cake,
where were you?

16:31.733 --> 16:33.491
I was on a spiritual quest.

16:33.568 --> 16:36.643
You were in Peru
tripping on ayahuasca.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.979
Oh, tomato, to-mah-to.

16:39.057 --> 16:40.647
Eileen...

16:40.725 --> 16:44.894
your daughter was in pain
because of your choices.

16:44.912 --> 16:46.653
You're either going to
acknowledge that,

16:46.673 --> 16:47.988
or you're not.

16:48.008 --> 16:50.583
I acknowledge
that you made your point.

16:50.735 --> 16:51.676
I'm a terrible mother,

16:51.827 --> 16:53.511
and she's better off
without me.

16:53.588 --> 16:56.922
I deserve to be invisible.

16:57.075 --> 16:58.016
Got it.

16:58.167 --> 17:00.018
Got it. Okay.

17:01.246 --> 17:04.522
<i> Ay, ay, ay.</i>
<i> Dios mío, esta señora.</i>

17:04.749 --> 17:09.027
Hi. Excuse me.
Um, you know Roarke's drink?

17:09.103 --> 17:12.012
Single malt.

17:12.032 --> 17:14.940
What are you hoping to buy
with that single malt?

17:15.017 --> 17:17.535
A phone call.

17:17.612 --> 17:19.111
It's just...

17:19.205 --> 17:21.447
I miss my family,
you know,

17:21.524 --> 17:25.025
and I just--I don't think she
really understands how much.

17:25.119 --> 17:27.211
(Latin music playing)

17:27.363 --> 17:29.530
You know, in all the years
I've been here,

17:29.549 --> 17:32.884
I've never flown her anywhere,
not one time.

17:32.960 --> 17:34.610
She understands.

17:34.612 --> 17:37.613
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:37.615 --> 17:39.640
Thanks, Javier.

17:42.787 --> 17:43.877
Hi, could I get a--

17:43.897 --> 17:45.454
EILEEN:
Wait, I know I'm invisible,

17:45.473 --> 17:49.308
but what do I have to do
to get a drink here?

17:49.460 --> 17:51.694
(groans)

17:53.798 --> 17:57.224
Hi, there, Eileen.

17:57.243 --> 17:59.243
Do you need anything?

17:59.395 --> 18:03.748
A drink, but I can't seem to
get the bartender's attention,

18:03.899 --> 18:05.750
what, with being invisible
and all.

18:05.827 --> 18:07.310
(chuckles)
Excuse me.

18:07.328 --> 18:09.736
Can we get
two passionfruit daiquiris?

18:09.756 --> 18:11.664
-But make one with a floater.
-I like you.

18:11.758 --> 18:14.592
You know, you have a much
better sense of hospitality

18:14.743 --> 18:15.835
than your boss.

18:15.987 --> 18:17.987
Oh, I like to think
that we, uh,

18:17.989 --> 18:19.655
you know,
complement one another.

18:19.674 --> 18:22.007
You know, it's not like
this invisibility thing

18:22.084 --> 18:23.676
is a new feeling.

18:23.828 --> 18:27.254
But this--I feel dead.

18:27.332 --> 18:28.589
Yeah.

18:28.666 --> 18:30.516
I know how you feel.

18:30.668 --> 18:32.001
That's kind, sweetie,

18:32.003 --> 18:33.927
but I have
crow's feet older than you.

18:33.947 --> 18:35.113
(laughs)

18:35.264 --> 18:37.931
Looks can be deceiving
around here.

18:37.951 --> 18:40.284
I'm a permanent resident
of the island now,

18:40.436 --> 18:43.679
but not too long ago,
I was a...

18:43.698 --> 18:46.198
75-year-old Black woman

18:46.351 --> 18:49.018
living in the suburbs
of Cincinnati

18:49.111 --> 18:52.296
dying of cancer.

18:53.708 --> 18:56.634
I mean, I know invisible.

18:57.879 --> 19:00.096
Yes, you do.

19:01.975 --> 19:04.033
Ah. Thank you.

19:04.035 --> 19:05.476
Wow.
(chuckles)

19:05.628 --> 19:07.536
Some island.

19:07.538 --> 19:10.373
Yes. (chuckles)
Well, I'll cheers to that.

19:10.375 --> 19:11.724
(chuckles)

19:11.800 --> 19:14.894
-You got kids?
-Mm, mm-hmm.

19:14.896 --> 19:18.138
Three and six grandkids,
well, so far.

19:18.158 --> 19:20.825
And do your children
blame you for everything?

19:20.860 --> 19:24.220
Our youngest put us
through it, okay?

19:24.238 --> 19:25.404
She went off to college

19:25.556 --> 19:28.407
and picked up a whole list
of grievances.

19:28.559 --> 19:31.076
You know, I mean,
I knew it was wrong

19:31.229 --> 19:33.562
to leave my grandson alone
in the house that night,

19:33.581 --> 19:37.341
but I couldn't bear it
a second longer.

19:37.418 --> 19:41.846
I felt so old,
irrelevant.

19:41.997 --> 19:44.348
I felt...

19:44.500 --> 19:45.558
Invisible?

19:47.503 --> 19:49.578
Yeah.

19:49.597 --> 19:51.889
And so I...

19:52.041 --> 19:55.601
followed the music,
just to be out,

19:55.753 --> 19:57.678
just to be seen,

19:57.697 --> 20:02.575
just to prove to myself that
I'm still here.

20:05.521 --> 20:07.521
And now
I've lost my daughter forever.

20:07.598 --> 20:11.617
Oh, well, look, you can't
change the past, right?

20:11.694 --> 20:16.288
So, if you screwed up then,
be there for her now,

20:16.365 --> 20:18.774
because when it comes
to being a parent,

20:18.867 --> 20:21.201
I mean, you can't stop trying.

20:21.221 --> 20:24.447
Even when your kid
slams the door in your face,

20:24.449 --> 20:27.225
it's your job to keep knocking.

20:29.896 --> 20:32.104
Did it work
with your daughter?

20:33.458 --> 20:35.900
(scoffs)
A little too well.

20:35.977 --> 20:38.069
She moved back home.

20:38.220 --> 20:41.989
-Hmm.
-(chuckles)

20:45.728 --> 20:48.895
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

20:48.915 --> 20:55.461
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:45.046 --> 21:48.881
What do we have here?

21:48.957 --> 21:55.646
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:12.999 --> 22:15.224
(exhales deeply)

22:15.226 --> 22:18.060
(doorknob rattling)

22:18.062 --> 22:19.986
This isn't funny, Roarke.

22:20.064 --> 22:22.581
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

22:22.733 --> 22:26.735
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:26.754 --> 22:30.573
Logic dictates that these are
cheap magic tricks.

22:30.666 --> 22:37.563
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:52.096 --> 22:54.497
-EILEEN: Watch it.
-Sorry.

22:56.542 --> 22:59.101
Can you speak?

22:59.120 --> 23:02.195
-EILEEN: Can you hear me?
-Say something.

23:02.273 --> 23:04.123
EILEEN: I just did.

23:04.125 --> 23:06.050
No, no, no.

23:06.201 --> 23:09.035
It happened on contact.

23:09.037 --> 23:10.721
Slap my hand again.

23:12.392 --> 23:15.284
How about this?

23:15.302 --> 23:18.020
Yes.

23:19.065 --> 23:21.065
It's touch.

23:21.142 --> 23:24.402
Hello, Eileen.

23:24.478 --> 23:26.645
I'm C-Charles.

23:26.722 --> 23:30.649
Would you be kind enough to
explain yourself,

23:30.801 --> 23:32.660
uh, if you can?

23:34.488 --> 23:36.488
Hi, Charles.

23:36.641 --> 23:38.732
Explain myself.

23:38.809 --> 23:42.253
Well, I'm invisible, obviously.

23:42.404 --> 23:45.256
It seems to be this
crazy island's idea of a joke

23:45.407 --> 23:49.677
or the literalization
of middle age and beyond.

23:50.763 --> 23:54.581
Anyhow, uh,
nice to meet you.

23:54.600 --> 23:56.175
And you as well.

23:56.327 --> 23:59.995
Would you stay
and talk with me a while?

23:59.997 --> 24:06.569
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:09.782 --> 24:11.097
(sighs)

24:11.117 --> 24:14.618
8:00 p.m., so I figured
you'd be at the office.

24:14.695 --> 24:18.030
I was--
I was just heading out.

24:18.106 --> 24:19.457
What's this?

24:19.533 --> 24:22.351
Oh, you know, just the best
single malt money can buy.

24:22.369 --> 24:25.111
-Oh.
-I thought we could talk.

24:25.189 --> 24:26.797
If this is about
calling Mel--

24:26.874 --> 24:28.114
No, no.

24:28.134 --> 24:30.784
Please, okay?
Please.

24:30.861 --> 24:33.879
I'm not gonna
ask you again.

24:34.031 --> 24:36.031
It's just...

24:36.033 --> 24:37.475
I want to know why.

24:37.551 --> 24:41.979
Look, I know being here
feels like...

24:42.130 --> 24:43.814
stumbling around
in a dark room

24:43.966 --> 24:46.150
and you're looking
for the light switch.

24:46.301 --> 24:48.986
But believe me
when I tell you...

24:49.137 --> 24:51.213
you're not gonna find one.

24:51.215 --> 24:53.974
Ruby, the only way forward

24:53.993 --> 24:56.577
is to follow the path
laid out for you here.

24:57.663 --> 24:59.905
You've been given
a second chance at life.

25:00.057 --> 25:01.406
Try to embrace it.

25:01.483 --> 25:04.409
<i> (soft acoustic guitar music)</i>

25:04.562 --> 25:06.820
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:06.897 --> 25:11.900
EILEEN: In through the nose
and out through the mouth.

25:11.902 --> 25:13.660
(exhales deeply)

25:13.679 --> 25:15.587
I'm--I'm failing to grasp
the significance of this.

25:15.664 --> 25:18.999
Shh!
Just breathe.

25:19.018 --> 25:22.411
(breathing deeply)

25:22.429 --> 25:23.746
I'm sorry.

25:23.764 --> 25:26.506
I have a bad back,
and this really isn't helping.

25:26.526 --> 25:27.933
I think we need to take

25:28.010 --> 25:30.586
a more scientific approach
to your problem.

25:30.604 --> 25:32.178
Science has nothing
to do with this.

25:32.198 --> 25:35.015
It's about my daughter.
She doesn't want to see me.

25:35.034 --> 25:37.517
Therefore, I'm invisible.

25:37.595 --> 25:40.262
I'm sure your predicament
can be explained somehow.

25:40.264 --> 25:41.688
(scoffs) You know, Charlie,
you strike me

25:41.766 --> 25:44.208
as someone who has suffered
from a lifelong inability

25:44.359 --> 25:47.436
to surrender
in any way to irrationality.

25:47.529 --> 25:50.047
It's Charles,
and you're correct.

25:50.198 --> 25:53.275
Well, Charles, I'm a woman,
not a lab experiment,

25:53.277 --> 25:55.035
and I want
to show you something.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.536
Do you believe in fate,
Charlie?

25:56.614 --> 25:58.055
CHARLES: The universe
doesn't care what we believe.

25:58.132 --> 26:01.392
-EILEEN: That's dark.
-It's really not, just factual.

26:01.468 --> 26:03.060
I think you were put
in my path

26:03.211 --> 26:05.304
for a very specific reason.

26:05.380 --> 26:07.565
Look.

26:09.293 --> 26:11.718
Voyeurism is risky business
for the non-transparent.

26:11.737 --> 26:14.980
It didn't stop you
last time.

26:15.132 --> 26:16.389
Who is she?

26:16.558 --> 26:19.726
Charles, she's my world,
and she's cut me out of hers.

26:19.820 --> 26:21.637
That's your daughter?
She's here on the island?

26:21.655 --> 26:24.306
Oh, I messed up,
and I need her to forgive me.

26:24.308 --> 26:25.899
Now, that's where you come in.

26:25.918 --> 26:27.751
-Me?
-Charles, you're going to talk

26:27.903 --> 26:29.645
to her and convince Theodora

26:29.663 --> 26:32.072
that I'm not all the terrible
things she thinks I am.

26:32.149 --> 26:34.407
All due respect,
I barely know you.

26:34.485 --> 26:36.151
Oh, I'll tell you
exactly what to say.

26:36.153 --> 26:38.578
Maybe you were
a terrible mother.

26:38.598 --> 26:41.506
-That's cruel.
-It's a logical supposition.

26:41.583 --> 26:44.084
If she's not talking to you,
there must be a reason.

26:44.161 --> 26:46.937
You sound like Roarke.
Everything is my fault.

26:47.164 --> 26:48.922
You know, I'm beginning
to get the feeling

26:48.941 --> 26:50.849
that you've been manipulating
me since the moment we met.

26:51.001 --> 26:52.501
For a good reason.

26:52.519 --> 26:54.111
In science,
we manipulate objects

26:54.262 --> 26:56.447
to see how they will react
in different scenarios,

26:56.598 --> 26:58.357
but I am not an object.

26:58.433 --> 27:00.859
No, you're a...

27:01.011 --> 27:05.164
lonely, closed-minded
stick in the mud.

27:08.294 --> 27:10.276
I'm a lonely, closed-minded
stick in the mud

27:10.354 --> 27:12.421
who is through
listening to you.

27:13.858 --> 27:18.010
And just like that, Eileen,
you no longer exist to me.

27:19.880 --> 27:21.639
Charles, wai--

27:25.052 --> 27:27.978
<i> (soft music)</i>

27:28.130 --> 27:31.890
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:31.984 --> 27:34.134
ELENA:
Leaving so soon?

27:34.153 --> 27:35.227
I've seen enough.

27:35.303 --> 27:38.805
That's an interesting
choice of words.

27:38.899 --> 27:40.215
You're talking about Eileen.

27:40.217 --> 27:42.217
Well, your desire
was to experience

27:42.219 --> 27:45.145
something unexplainable.

27:45.222 --> 27:46.997
So can you explain it?

27:47.074 --> 27:49.391
(scoffs)
Her invisibility?

27:49.393 --> 27:50.984
With time, I'm sure I could.

27:51.061 --> 27:53.504
The rest of her?
Absolutely not.

27:53.655 --> 27:56.173
You know what I see
when I...

27:56.400 --> 27:59.009
when I look at Eileen?

27:59.161 --> 28:01.904
I see someone in pain.

28:01.906 --> 28:04.239
When I look at you...

28:04.258 --> 28:06.591
I see the same thing.

28:06.744 --> 28:09.186
That's why I keep feeling
you can help each other.

28:09.337 --> 28:11.171
(scoffs)
I don't know how.

28:11.248 --> 28:12.523
We have nothing in common.

28:12.599 --> 28:14.358
For one, you both struggle

28:14.435 --> 28:16.084
to see other people's
points of view.

28:16.086 --> 28:17.695
That's not--

28:19.031 --> 28:21.281
That might be true.

28:22.776 --> 28:25.185
Do you always do that,
Professor?

28:25.204 --> 28:28.288
Do you always shut down
when people push you?

28:30.267 --> 28:32.876
Maybe that's why...

28:33.028 --> 28:35.045
you're so alone.

28:36.457 --> 28:40.217
This has nothing to do
with my fantasy.

28:40.368 --> 28:42.219
Okay.

28:42.446 --> 28:43.946
Or does it?

28:43.948 --> 28:50.728
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:08.063 --> 29:10.038
CHARLES:
May I?

29:13.143 --> 29:14.810
EILEEN:
Sure.

29:14.812 --> 29:21.592
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:28.325 --> 29:30.559
I'm sorry.
I was out of line.

29:32.830 --> 29:36.256
No, you were right about me.

29:36.333 --> 29:38.275
Theodora is right about me.

29:38.426 --> 29:40.093
I am selfish.

29:40.112 --> 29:43.614
I always think
about myself first,

29:43.765 --> 29:48.844
and I don't think
about how other people feel.

29:48.862 --> 29:50.512
And now Theodora hates me,

29:50.531 --> 29:55.125
and I am so sorry
I sucked you into it all.

29:55.277 --> 29:59.004
You seem like
a very nice man, and...

30:00.115 --> 30:02.524
You deserve better.

30:02.543 --> 30:05.877
-Can I confess something?
-Of course.

30:06.030 --> 30:08.788
I'm having fun.

30:08.866 --> 30:12.142
(chuckles)
Um, me too.

30:12.219 --> 30:15.053
I mean, I'm miserable, but...

30:15.130 --> 30:17.648
I get a kick
out of you, Charles.

30:17.799 --> 30:18.965
Hmm.

30:18.984 --> 30:20.334
I wish I could see you.

30:20.336 --> 30:23.895
Well, the irony is
that if you could see me,

30:24.048 --> 30:27.157
you might look
right through me.

30:27.309 --> 30:29.551
I'm a bit older than you.

30:29.570 --> 30:32.737
Eileen, I suspect
I would see you anywhere.

30:32.890 --> 30:39.461
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:08.033 --> 31:10.701
Let me help you with Theo.

31:10.777 --> 31:12.761
Are you sure?

31:12.779 --> 31:14.371
I'm certain.

31:14.522 --> 31:17.190
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:17.284 --> 31:18.934
<i> DAVID:</i>
<i> There was a shell kingdom,</i>

31:18.952 --> 31:21.119
and there was a crab kingdom,

31:21.213 --> 31:23.714
and then there was
a lobster kingdom.

31:23.790 --> 31:24.864
(sighs)
Ready?

31:24.942 --> 31:27.776
Definitely not,
but let's do it anyway.

31:27.778 --> 31:30.278
(laughs)
Mwah.

31:30.280 --> 31:33.782
<i> (quirky music)</i>

31:33.800 --> 31:40.713
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:40.733 --> 31:41.973
(laughs)
Oh.

31:42.050 --> 31:43.458
Sorry to bother you.

31:43.477 --> 31:45.143
I think this might belong
to the little guy.

31:45.220 --> 31:46.478
Okay, thanks.

31:46.630 --> 31:49.222
I could have sworn
I saw that on our grass.

31:49.241 --> 31:51.149
I'm Charles. Charlie.

31:51.226 --> 31:52.910
My friends call me Charlie.

31:52.986 --> 31:55.895
Theo.
Thanks again.

31:55.915 --> 31:58.640
Short for Theodora?

31:58.642 --> 32:01.567
-Yes, actually.
-CHARLES: Such a unique name.

32:01.587 --> 32:04.254
My friend Eileen has a daughter
named Theodora about your age.

32:04.331 --> 32:06.089
-DAVID: Eileen Mitchell?
-Yes.

32:06.166 --> 32:09.092
Are you--
It seems you are.

32:09.169 --> 32:10.652
What a small world.

32:10.654 --> 32:12.095
Yeah, you know my mother.

32:12.172 --> 32:14.765
What a coincidence.
How'd you two meet?

32:14.992 --> 32:17.417
How did we meet?
We, uh...

32:17.436 --> 32:18.751
We met at a conference.

32:18.829 --> 32:21.104
-We met at a conference.
-A conference for what?

32:21.181 --> 32:22.831
-Sustainable--
-Sustainable farming.

32:22.849 --> 32:24.015
-Fashion.
-Fashion.

32:24.168 --> 32:26.334
My mother,
who you're friends with?

32:26.336 --> 32:29.112
Yes, my friend Eileen,
your mother.

32:29.189 --> 32:32.932
When was the last time
you saw her?

32:33.010 --> 32:34.192
Tell her we had the duck bacon

32:34.344 --> 32:36.269
at Jack's Wife Freda
three weekends ago.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.680
We had duck bacon
with Jack and Frida.

32:38.699 --> 32:40.440
THEO:
And you're 100% sure

32:40.459 --> 32:42.108
she's not here
on this island right now?

32:42.186 --> 32:43.351
If she is,
I haven't seen her.

32:43.353 --> 32:46.946
-You're a liar.
-(chuckles) That's not a lie.

32:46.966 --> 32:48.690
-Honey, just--
-Don't, David.

32:48.709 --> 32:51.784
I could smell Eileen's perfume
on him the moment he walked up.

32:51.804 --> 32:54.262
Where is she?

32:59.553 --> 33:02.053
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

33:02.130 --> 33:03.814
Charles, say something.

33:03.965 --> 33:06.299
I don't know what to say.

33:06.318 --> 33:08.151
THEO: Is she planning to make
some grand entrance?

33:08.303 --> 33:10.136
Barge in, shower Freddy
in presents,

33:10.214 --> 33:11.880
then disappear again?

33:11.898 --> 33:13.806
-I should go.
-Yes, you should.

33:13.826 --> 33:15.734
Yeah, let's go.

33:15.810 --> 33:19.387
Thank you for trying.
I'll figure out another way.

33:19.389 --> 33:21.740
Before I go, one more thing,
if I may?

33:21.816 --> 33:23.558
Charles, it's no use.

33:23.560 --> 33:26.169
I made too big
of a mess of things.

33:26.396 --> 33:28.063
Eileen...

33:28.065 --> 33:30.490
please.

33:30.509 --> 33:33.418
I've known your mother
for a very short time,

33:33.570 --> 33:35.253
and in that time,

33:35.405 --> 33:38.664
I've seen how she will bulldoze
over anything

33:38.742 --> 33:39.924
to get what she wants.

33:40.043 --> 33:42.168
In fact, other than myself,
I've never met anyone

33:42.187 --> 33:44.337
so certain that their opinion
is the correct one.

33:44.414 --> 33:46.248
I'm standing right here.

33:46.266 --> 33:50.694
That said, uh, I also know
that Eileen loves you,

33:50.771 --> 33:53.438
Theo, and your family.

33:53.590 --> 33:55.348
I know that the only thing
she wants in this world

33:55.367 --> 33:57.259
is for you
to give her another chance,

33:57.352 --> 33:59.018
even if she doesn't deserve it.

33:59.096 --> 34:01.354
I'm hoping
you'll give it to her

34:01.431 --> 34:03.431
and let her show you
she's changed.

34:03.450 --> 34:05.542
She hasn't.

34:05.619 --> 34:08.736
This whole thing
is perfectly on brand.

34:08.772 --> 34:11.940
Once again, I am hanging on
to the runaway train

34:12.033 --> 34:13.458
that is the Eileen show.

34:13.610 --> 34:15.627
It's always about her needs,
her desires.

34:15.779 --> 34:18.538
It's like I'm invisible to her.

34:18.615 --> 34:21.283
EILEEN: You're right.
You've always been right.

34:21.301 --> 34:23.451
It was wrong of me
to leave Freddy alone

34:23.470 --> 34:26.121
and go to the neighbors'
for karaoke,

34:26.139 --> 34:28.381
just as it was wrong of me
to leave you

34:28.400 --> 34:31.050
-at the Golden Lotus.
-THEO: Mom, is that you?

34:31.128 --> 34:33.403
Babe, you okay?

34:35.390 --> 34:38.241
(voice breaking)
Every time you left,

34:38.318 --> 34:41.303
I was convinced
you weren't coming back.

34:41.321 --> 34:45.156
How could I,
your backpack of a daughter,

34:45.233 --> 34:47.417
compete
with your glamorous life?

34:47.494 --> 34:51.254
EILEEN: Theodora, darling girl,
you are my life.

34:51.331 --> 34:52.738
I'm sorry that I was selfish,

34:52.833 --> 34:55.908
and you don't need to forgive
me if you're not ready.

34:55.928 --> 34:58.411
but just know
that I am never going to stop

34:58.488 --> 35:01.673
trying to make
this right, ever.

35:01.767 --> 35:03.158
Mom, wait.

35:03.160 --> 35:06.269
<i> (pleasant music)</i>

35:06.421 --> 35:11.757
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:11.835 --> 35:14.927
(chuckles)

35:14.929 --> 35:16.279
(scoffs)

35:16.431 --> 35:18.539
I don't understand
what just happened.

35:18.541 --> 35:22.268
I really didn't mean to make
a grand entrance this time.

35:22.287 --> 35:23.695
(both laugh)

35:23.771 --> 35:25.580
I believe you.

35:27.775 --> 35:29.775
It's a long story.

35:29.795 --> 35:31.703
Charles can--

35:31.779 --> 35:36.191
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:36.193 --> 35:38.042
I want to hear
everything,

35:38.195 --> 35:41.621
but first,
I got to get in my snuggles.

35:41.698 --> 35:43.882
Oh, Freddy.

35:44.034 --> 35:46.050
Oh, Freddy.
Mwah.

35:46.127 --> 35:48.478
You feel so good.

35:56.897 --> 35:58.572
Hi.

36:00.325 --> 36:03.677
You ran off before
I had a chance to thank you.

36:03.679 --> 36:06.663
I wanted to give you
some time with your family.

36:06.740 --> 36:08.832
I'm happy for you.

36:08.909 --> 36:12.410
You know, I just realized
that I've been thinking so much

36:12.562 --> 36:13.578
about myself,

36:13.730 --> 36:16.590
I didn't even ask
what your fantasy was.

36:18.418 --> 36:22.328
You know, Eileen,
I think it was you.

36:22.406 --> 36:24.589
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:24.666 --> 36:27.091
(chuckles)

36:27.168 --> 36:29.335
This feels wrong.

36:29.413 --> 36:30.912
What does?

36:30.931 --> 36:32.931
Not holding hands.

36:33.083 --> 36:35.417
(laughs)

36:35.419 --> 36:41.847
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:41.867 --> 36:44.759
(both laugh)

36:44.761 --> 36:46.277
(groans)

36:46.354 --> 36:49.447
<i> (upbeat tropical music)</i>

36:49.599 --> 36:52.709
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:52.786 --> 36:57.288
(laughter)

36:57.441 --> 36:59.883
Now, that's my kind
of breakfast.

36:59.960 --> 37:01.384
Okay.

37:01.536 --> 37:03.127
I'm sorry.
Why was I invited to this?

37:03.280 --> 37:05.204
Um, I imagine we'll find out.

37:05.282 --> 37:09.226
-(glass clinking)
-I'd like to make a toast.

37:09.377 --> 37:12.211
This has truly been
a transformative week--

37:12.231 --> 37:14.064
one that would not
have been possible

37:14.140 --> 37:17.717
without the formidable talents
of Elena...

37:17.736 --> 37:19.294
(laughter)

37:19.312 --> 37:20.886
EILEEN:
Or the wise counsel of Ruby.

37:20.964 --> 37:21.980
Oh, thank you.

37:22.132 --> 37:23.389
EILEEN:
And, Javier,

37:23.408 --> 37:26.317
I'm so sorry that I wasted
your time the other day.

37:26.470 --> 37:29.471
I'll write a check to you
for the fuel.

37:29.473 --> 37:32.064
-Don't mention it.
-(laughter)

37:32.142 --> 37:34.659
You know, sometimes in life,

37:34.753 --> 37:38.255
the most important lessons
are the hardest to learn,

37:38.331 --> 37:40.315
but if you put in the work,

37:40.333 --> 37:43.318
it can yield
the sweetest rewards.

37:43.320 --> 37:46.488
And I'm going to keep working

37:46.506 --> 37:49.507
-so I can hold on to it.
-(laughter)

37:49.659 --> 37:51.751
I'm not sure what you did
with my mom,

37:51.828 --> 37:53.970
but I think I'll keep this one,
if you don't mind.

37:54.047 --> 37:55.939
Okay.

37:56.016 --> 37:58.182
You're so funny, Theodora.

37:58.277 --> 37:59.834
You'd kill them
at the Catskills.

37:59.836 --> 38:02.020
-Oh, and there she is.
-(laughter)

38:02.188 --> 38:04.281
So what's next
for the Mitchell clan?

38:04.357 --> 38:07.433
Oh, Charles had
a brilliant idea.

38:07.452 --> 38:10.028
I suggested we stick around
for a proper vacation

38:10.104 --> 38:12.514
with somewhat less
inexplicable phenomena.

38:12.532 --> 38:13.848
Oh, on this island?

38:13.867 --> 38:16.609
I don't think
we can guarantee that.

38:16.686 --> 38:18.110
Maybe not,

38:18.130 --> 38:20.872
but I can guarantee you
a wonderful time.

38:20.948 --> 38:22.923
-RUBY: Mm.
-Well, then...

38:22.925 --> 38:24.283
to a wonderful time...

38:24.361 --> 38:27.971
but, more importantly,
to family.

38:28.048 --> 38:29.864
ALL:
To family.

38:29.883 --> 38:36.730
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:38.058 --> 38:41.818
(laughter, indistinct chatter)

38:41.895 --> 38:44.303
Ruby, come with me.

38:44.381 --> 38:47.048
I want to show you something.

38:47.141 --> 38:50.327
(chatter continues)

38:51.905 --> 38:53.997
Surprise.

38:54.074 --> 38:56.224
My chair.

38:56.226 --> 38:58.242
-Oh, no.
-(door closes)

38:58.395 --> 39:00.912
Oh, wow.

39:01.064 --> 39:05.508
Oh, yes. I love this chair.

39:05.660 --> 39:07.585
Oh.

39:07.662 --> 39:10.922
Oh, my goodness.

39:10.998 --> 39:13.391
Oh, the painting.

39:15.020 --> 39:17.336
-Oh.
-ELENA: And here.

39:17.414 --> 39:21.583
These are recent,
since you left.

39:21.585 --> 39:24.510
<i> (heartwarming music)</i>

39:24.588 --> 39:25.920
Oh.

39:25.922 --> 39:29.532
Wow. Look at him.

39:29.609 --> 39:32.093
(chuckles)

39:32.095 --> 39:35.279
There go my babies
right there.

39:35.432 --> 39:36.614
Mm-hmm.

39:36.766 --> 39:38.766
(chuckles)

39:38.768 --> 39:43.195
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:43.215 --> 39:46.774
ELENA: Um, you have a note
from--from Mel.

39:46.793 --> 39:47.792
Oh.

39:47.944 --> 39:54.724
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:59.898 --> 40:02.273
Oh.
(chuckles)

40:04.794 --> 40:07.145
I'll, um...

40:07.221 --> 40:10.723
I'll make sure you get one,
you know, every now and then.

40:10.800 --> 40:13.910
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:14.061 --> 40:18.640
How did you do this?

40:18.642 --> 40:19.565
You know what?

40:19.584 --> 40:21.251
Oh, um...

40:21.327 --> 40:23.711
I don't even want to know.
(chuckles)

40:25.757 --> 40:27.315
One more thing...

40:27.333 --> 40:29.926
Mel--he wanted you
to have this.

40:30.003 --> 40:31.986
Oh, yes.

40:31.988 --> 40:33.321
That's, uh...

40:33.414 --> 40:36.766
my 20th anniversary present.
(chuckles)

40:36.843 --> 40:38.493
This means the world to me.

40:38.511 --> 40:40.511
It's beautiful.

40:40.664 --> 40:43.756
Oh, God.

40:43.833 --> 40:46.334
But what about, um...

40:46.352 --> 40:49.671
embracing the future,
you know,

40:49.673 --> 40:51.781
not looking back?

40:51.933 --> 40:55.359
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:55.512 --> 40:58.938
Sometimes you have to meet
people where they are.

40:59.015 --> 41:01.349
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:01.367 --> 41:02.867
(sniffles)

41:02.944 --> 41:04.352
Well...

41:04.354 --> 41:07.188
how about I make us
some tea...

41:07.190 --> 41:08.965
(sniffles, chuckles)

41:09.042 --> 41:11.526
And bore you
with baby pictures?

41:11.544 --> 41:14.119
-I would love that.
-(both laugh)

41:14.197 --> 41:17.807
-There you go.
-Ah.

41:17.884 --> 41:20.810
Ruby, they're stunning.

41:20.887 --> 41:23.554
Thank you.

41:23.707 --> 41:25.464
(chuckles)

41:25.484 --> 41:30.028
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
